<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF76FBF1FD4AFB70" blockId="64.[151,1437,1143,1890]" box="[151,682,1143,1170]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Size. Known adult size about 
<quantity id="2E379B383F75FFE2FE07FBF1FDFDFB73" box="[486,541,1143,1170]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="cm" value="9.0">9 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F75FFE2FF26FB1DFC89F883" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FB1DFDB4FAC0" blockId="64.[151,1437,1143,1890]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Morphology. D VI + I,13–16; A I,13–15; P 18–20. Medium-sized goby with moderately elongate body, large head, and a short, slightly acute and oblique snout. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin may be slightly higher in appearance, with more or less rounded distal edge and no elongate spines. Caudal fin rounded.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FAADFB02FAA4" blockId="64.[151,1437,1143,1890]" box="[199,1250,1323,1350]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Scales present on body and on predorsal area, usually visible on photographs at least on body.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26FAC9FCCCF9A0" blockId="64.[151,1437,1143,1890]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FE67FAC9FDFAFA6C" bold="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Head yellowish, more intensely on the snout and in the interorbital space, contrasting with a light gray or whitish body</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FDC8FAF5FD9CFA6C" box="[553,636,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="36.[151,250,972,996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,948]" captionTargetId="figure-19@36.[164,1423,181,948]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 38. A) Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius xanthocephalus. B) Upper lip with at least one orange mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on upper border of eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photos by P. Louisy, Banyuls, Pyrénées Orientales, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601685/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Head and body covered with longitudinal lines of well-defined orange to dark red dots. Eyes with brown stripes radiating from the pupil over iris to the orbital rim, 2 of them constituting a broad horizontal stripe across the pupil; 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FDB8FA3DFEFDFA18" bold="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">the upper eye radial stripes are connected by an irregular longitudinal curved line</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FECCFA59FE70FA1B" box="[301,400,1503,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="36.[151,250,972,996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,948]" captionTargetId="figure-19@36.[164,1423,181,948]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 38. A) Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius xanthocephalus. B) Upper lip with at least one orange mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on upper border of eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photos by P. Louisy, Banyuls, Pyrénées Orientales, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601685/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 38b</figureCitation>
). Upper lip with orange markings. Lower lip with a median W-shaped mark. Snout with Mshaped line and an oblique preorbital bar (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FD9CF985FD02F9FF" box="[637,738,1539,1566]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="36.[151,250,972,996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,948]" captionTargetId="figure-19@36.[164,1423,181,948]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 38. A) Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius xanthocephalus. B) Upper lip with at least one orange mark in addition to the dot on the corner of the mouth; dark curved mark on upper border of eye connects longitudinally other marks. Photos by P. Louisy, Banyuls, Pyrénées Orientales, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601685" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601685/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 38b</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FD16F985FD4FF9A0" bold="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">One isolated brown to dark red dot at the corner of the mouth, followed by 2 short horizontal dashes</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F75FFE2FD5FF9A1FCFFF9A0" box="[702,799,1575,1601]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 33. The mouth unmarked at corner in A) G. bucchichi and B) H. ingressus. Dark dot on the corner of the mouth in C) G. auratus, D) G. incognitus, E) G. xanthocephalus and F) G. fallax. Area marked with hollow circle. Photos by R. Svensen (A), S. Engin (B), M. Kovačić (C, D, F), and P. Louisy (E). C and F photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601673/files/figure.png" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Fig. 33e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26F9CDFCE9F987" blockId="64.[151,1437,1143,1890]" box="[199,777,1611,1638]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
