<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FCB3F9E9FB87F968" author="Heymer, A. &amp; Zander, C. D." box="[850,1127,1647,1673]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="291 - 314" refId="ref56320" refString="Heymer, A. &amp; Zander, C. D. (1992) Le statut de Gobius auratus Risso, 1810 et description de Gobius xanthocephalus n. sp. de la Mediterranee (Teleostei, Gobiidae). Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolution, 119, 291 - 314." type="journal article" year="1992">Heymer &amp; Zander 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FB95F9E9FA90F96B" author="Wirtz, P. &amp; Herrera, R." box="[1140,1392,1647,1674]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="115 - 118" refId="ref66088" refString="Wirtz, P. &amp; Herrera, R. (1995) The lobster Enoplometopus antillensis (Decapoda: Enoplometopidae) and the goby Gobius xanthocephalus (Pisces: Gobiidae) - new records for the marine fauna of the Canary Islands. Arquipelago, Life and Marine Sciences, 13 A, 115 - 118." type="journal article" year="1995">Wirtz &amp; Herrera 1995</bibRefCitation>
) on hard (e.g., bedrock, coralligenous) or mixed bottoms (e.g., sandy patches with pebbles, boulders, and seagrass).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F75FFE2FF26F931FC89F883" blockId="64.[151,1437,1143,1890]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
Geographic distribution. Northeastern Atlantic, Mediterranean and Black Sea. In the Mediterranean, recorded in the northwestern Mediterranean (Miller 1986), including the Balearic Island of Ibiza (Fisher 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FB77F95AFB25F914" box="[1174,1221,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2007) and 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F75FFE2FAA6F95DFA7DF914" box="[1351,1437,1755,1781]" name="France" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Corsica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FF7EF979FE6AF8F8" author="Francour, P. &amp; Bodilis, P. &amp; Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C." box="[159,394,1791,1818]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref54712" refString="Francour, P., Bodilis, P., Cottalorda, J. M. &amp; Seytre, C. (2010) Inventaire des Gobiidae dans la Reiserve Naturelle de Scandola (Corse) et aI proximitei de ses limites. Contrat Parc Naturel Reigional de la Corse. Universitei de Nice-Sophia Antipolis, ECOMERS publ., Nice, 1 - 54." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Francour 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FEECF886FEDFF8F8" box="[269,319,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Isolated populations confirmed in Crimea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FC61F979FB95F8F8" author="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P. &amp; Danilyuk, O. N." box="[896,1141,1791,1818]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="277 - 291" refId="ref52329" refString="Boltachev, A. R., Karpova, E. P. &amp; Danilyuk, O. N. (2009) Findings of new and rare fish species in the coastal zone of the Crimea (the Black Sea). Journal of Ichthyology, 49 (4), 277 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0032945209040018" type="journal article" year="2009">
Boltachev 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F75FFE2FC1AF886FBCDF8F8" box="[1019,1069,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
) and in the eastern part of the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FEDFF8A5FD78F8DC" author="Vasil'eva, E. D. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V." box="[318,664,1827,1853]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="599 - 606" refId="ref65850" refString="Vasil'eva, E. D. &amp; Bogorodsky, S. V. (2004) Two new species of gobies (Gobiidae) in the ichthyofauna of the Black Sea. Journal of Ichthyology, 44, 599 - 606." type="journal article" year="2004">Vasil’eva &amp; Bogorodsky 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In the Atlantic Ocean: from Galicia, Northern Spain (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FB1BF8A5FEB5F880" author="Villegas-Riios, D. &amp; BanToin, R." pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="311 - 314" refId="ref65892" refString="Villegas-Riios, D. &amp; BanToin, R. (2010) First record and new meristic data of Gobius xanthocephalus (Gobiidae) from Galician waters (NW Spain). Cybium, 34 (3), 311 - 314. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2010 - 343 - 010" type="journal article" year="2010">Villegas-Riìos &amp; BanÞoìn 2010</bibRefCitation>
) to the Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F75FFE2FDBEF8C1FCBCF883" author="Wirtz, P. &amp; Herrera, R." box="[607,860,1863,1890]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="115 - 118" refId="ref66088" refString="Wirtz, P. &amp; Herrera, R. (1995) The lobster Enoplometopus antillensis (Decapoda: Enoplometopidae) and the goby Gobius xanthocephalus (Pisces: Gobiidae) - new records for the marine fauna of the Canary Islands. Arquipelago, Life and Marine Sciences, 13 A, 115 - 118." type="journal article" year="1995">Wirtz &amp; Herrera 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
